# Tailwind primary color

This project defines a semantic Tailwind color `primary` in `tailwind.config.ts`.

## Rules

- Do **not** hardcode brand colors via `bg-[#...]`, `text-[#...]`, `border-[#...]`, `ring-[#...]`.
- Use semantic classes instead:
  - `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `border-primary`, `ring-primary`
  - hover/active: `hover:bg-primary-600`, `active:bg-primary-700`
  - light backgrounds: `bg-primary-50`, `bg-primary-100`

## Examples

Bad:

`class="bg-[#E25E2D] hover:bg-[#C84E24]"`

Good:

`class="bg-primary hover:bg-primary-600 active:bg-primary-700"`

